The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, February 17, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, February 17, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	BT Road to Bidhan Sarani after 2 pm. Bustee Federation on protest march to demand civic amenities.				 																																	Clive Row from 2.30 pm. Nationalised bank employees to demonstrate.				 																Soiree				 																																	Ramakrishna Sarada Mission, Siriti, presents a classical music programme to mark the 150th birth anniversary of Sri Sri Sarada Devi at Kala Mandir, 5.30 pm. Songs by Haimanti Shukla, sarod recital by Tejendra Narayan Majumdar, accompanied on tabla by Anindo Chatterjee. 				 																Pen skills				 																																	Short course on dramatic writing at the Indian Institute of Cerebral Palsy, in collaboration with British Council, from 10 am.				 																Aid project				 																																	US consul-general George N. Sibley to inaugurate a project of Tiljala Society for Human amp; Educational Development at Childrens Park, JK Ghose Road, 10.30 am.				 																Film fare				 																																	Screenings, as part of the 3rd International Social Communication Cinema Conference, at Nandan II and III, from 10.30 am to 5.30 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	Watercolours by Paresh Maity on display at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.				 																																	Inauguration of a painting exhibition by Ritendra Roy at Birla Academy of Art and Culture, 5.30 pm. 				 																																	Works of painter Gobinda Chandra Mondal are on display at Gaganendra Pradarshashala, 2 to 8 pm.
